Function Reference/get tag link « WordPress Codex
-----------

Returns the correct link url for a given Tag ID.

Usage
-----

` <a href=\"<?php echo get_tag_link($tag_id); ?>\">tag name</a>`

Parameters
----------

 tag\_id 
:   (*numeric*) The Tag ID.

Return Values
-------------

 (URL) 
:   `(string)` URL with a link to the tag.

Filters
-------

Output from this function is
[filtered](/Plugin_API/Filter_Reference "Plugin API/Filter Reference")
by the 'tag\_link' filter. The first argument (\$taglink) is the url as
the function would normally output it, the second is the ID passed into
the function.

    apply_filters('tag_link', $taglink, $tag_id);

Source File
-----------

`get_tag_link()` is located in `wp-includes/category-template.php`.

